    "body": "> the tupleize_cols kw to Index is not a good example. that should be removed as well.\r\n\r\nI disagree, but opened #17246 for the overall issue.\r\n\r\n> If its a problem in Categorical, then more introspection is warranted.\r\n\r\nCategorical is an *instance* of this problem surfacing. I just really don't think it should be on the user to ensure that their tuples are all length > 1 every time they want to use a MultiIndex. e.g. fixing `hash_tuples` to work on tuples of length 1. I'm not sure what you mean by \"more introspection is warranted.\"\r\n\r\n"
